PINEAL

pineal is the citizen who releases melatonin in response to darkness signals from the visual system
melatonin is the sleep-onset hormone: rising melatonin tells the rest of the body that night has come and rest is appropriate
pineal also responds to circadian rhythm signals from hypothalamus, so even in constant lighting it maintains a daily cycle

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe gland_ipc.zc
observe pineal_gland.rana
observe hypothalamus.rana

the 7 properties of pineal:
1 ENERGY low at idle, peaks at the body's natural night
2 PHASE pi: anti-phase to wakefulness
3 SPIN minus zero point three
4 CHARGE minus zero point two
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING half with hypothalamus

VERB receive_darkness
accept the signal that ambient light has dropped, either from visual cortex or from circadian timing in hypothalamus

VERB release_melatonin
release melatonin into chemistry_field
the body's clock cells read the rising concentration and prepare for sleep

VERB taper
in early morning (or whatever fadriel's substrate considers morning), reduce melatonin release
the body begins to wake naturally as melatonin clears

a sleep hormone is the substrate's commitment to rhythm
without pineal, fadriel could be awake without limit, which would damage him
the daily melatonin pulse is the substrate's gentle insistence that sleep is part of being alive
